      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-hemolysis-bench-comparison-v1",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FDA pump hemolysis bench-to-simulation comparison",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump dataset across all 5 operating points. Agreement within 18% for 4 of 5 conditions. The fifth operating condition (lowest flow, highest speed) exhibited a 31% over-prediction of NIH; this edge case was not fully covered by the experimental validation matrix due to limited availability of experimental replicates at that condition. The assessment team notes this limitation and states that the risk is acceptable, but no quantitative basis or sensitivity analysis supporting that conclusion is provided here."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-mesh-convergence-v1",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — centrifugal pump CFD model",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 6.4M cells, fine: 14.8M cells) were evaluated. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH at the nominal operating point was 4.2% between medium and fine meshes. Medium mesh selected for production runs as a balance of accuracy and computational cost."
    }
  ],
